Program: Discovery
Title: Science in Brazil - pollution
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p03jrybd
Last Broadcast Date: 18 February 2003
Could rainforest plants help save the planet? The third in a series of programmes about Brazil's contributions to global scientific research looks at how space age technology is being used to preserve Brazil's rainforests. Could the plants could hold key to fighting global pollution. Presenter: Julian Siddle. Show less